720450f-a.title: Manhattan: Horatio Street - Hudson Street
720450f-a.text:
Horatio Street, north side, from Hudson to Greenwich Streets,
inclusive. The corner lot, occupied by the gas station, would be
the site of No. 637 Hudson Street and 43 Horatio Street; it has been
vacant of buildings for a number of years.
March 29, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720449f-b.title: Manhattan: Horatio Street - Hudson Street
720449f-b.text:
Horatio Street, north side, from Hudson to 4th Streets, inclusive.
The lot on the N.W. corner of Hudson Street, where No. 637 Hudson
Street should stand, has been vacant for over twelve years at the
time of this picture. It includes what would be No. 43 Horatio Street.
The tall building at the N.W. corner of 4th Street is the Riker-
Hegeman Building.
March 12, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
